how do you overcome being rejected by the only one you love my ex and i were married for ten years wife the first was crazy i waited ten years between marraiges and was certain i would grow old with this person she decided she did not want to be married to me anymore there was is nothing to do you cannot control what the other person does even if you could would you would you wish for them to stay with you even if they are not happy my answer was no i can only speak from personal experience but i say this let them go on with their life and you must go on with yours the hurt never really goes away but it does get better here i am four years later and into marraige number three and have a very loving wife who practically worships me and i her i do not deserve this but this is what i got god only knows what she sees in me i am not asking any questions i am just thankful i have the lady i want in my life who wants to be with me i say to you move on do not keep your life on hold for an unreasonable amount of time you must take care of you and your needs wish this person well but do not waste your life away pining over somone who will not reciprocate the love you have i know it can be difficult but when the right person comes along you will soon wonder why you waited so long again i speak from experience here there will be when you least expect it a person who is just nuts about you and hopefully you will be available for them i hope this helps and i have the best of wishes for you Religious Society of Friends Marriage Ten Commandments God Pitaten Trinity Theory of conduct Altruism Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Jon Secada T. S. Eliot John Howard Yoder Shaggy dog story One Tree Hill (TV series) Love Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints A Course In Miracles Miss Saigon Meaning of life Divorce Criticisms of Charismatic and Pentecostal belief Polygamy The Amber Spyglass Prayer Marie de Rabutin-Chantal, marquise de S__vign__ Alcoholics Anonymous Inc